FT  20 OCT 93 / World News in Brief: Bomb terrorist jailed
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
IRA terrorist Patrick Kelly was jailed for 25 years at the Old Bailey for
plotting a bomb attack in central London and attempting to murder the
policeman who foiled him. Kelly, 41, was arrested while driving a lorry bomb
in Stoke Newington, north London.
