FT  20 OCT 93 / World News in Brief: IRA offers concessions
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Gerry Adams (left), leader of Sinn Fein, the political wing of the IRA, said
the Republican movement was ready to make concessions to bring an end to 24
years of violence in Ulster and that he wanted to see the IRA 'in permanent
retirement'. Prime minister John Major will hear from the Irish government
next week details of the recent peace initiative created by Mr Adams and
John Hume of the Social Democratic and Labour party.
