<HEADLINE>
FT  19 OCT 93 / International Company News: AHP profits rise 4% to Dollars
397.6m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By KAREN ZAGOR
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
AMERICAN Home Products, the US pharmaceutical company, yesterday posted a 4
per cent gain in third-quarter net income to Dollars 397.6m from Dollars
382.4m on sales up 3 per cent to Dollars 2.17bn from Dollars 2.11bn.
Earnings per share advanced 5 per cent to Dollars 1.28 from Dollars 1.22 in
the same period of 1992.
Pharmaceuticals, which account for most of the group's turnover, saw sales
slide 1 per cent to Dollars 1.19bn in the quarter.
US pharmaceutical sales advanced only 2 per cent in the latest quarter.
Sales of anti-inflammatory products grew following the introduction of
Lodine 400, and helped to offset decreased sales of the group's infant
nutritional products.
International pharmaceutical sales fell 5 per cent in the quarter,
reflecting unfavourable foreign exchange rates and weaker economies in some
of the company's key foreign markets.
Sales of consumer health care products rose 6 per cent to Dollars 493.4m in
the quarter, led by strong growth overseas, while those of medical supplies
and diagnostic products also grew 6 per cent to Dollars 216m.
For the first nine months, net income stood at Dollars 1.09bn, or Dollars
3.50 on sales of Dollars 6.19bn. A year earlier, the company reported net
income of Dollars 1.1bn, or Dollars 3.49, including charges for accounting
changes and for acquired research.
Stripping out these charges from last year's results, net income rose 8 per
cent in the first nine months of this year.
