FT  19 OCT 93 / International Company News: Publicis in share swap expansion
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ALICE RAWSTHORN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
PUBLICIS, one of France's leading marketing services groups, is expanding
its interests by merging with FCA], one of the few remaining independent
French advertising agencies, in a share swap deal.
The merger, which will leave Publicis with a majority interest in the
combined company, follows months of negotiations in which FCA] has tried to
find an international partner.
FCA], the fourth largest advertising agency in France, which also has an
international network, fell into the red last year following a fraud
perpetrated by an executive who is now in prison. It held talks with
McCann-Erickson, one of the largest agencies within Interpublic, the US
marketing group, but eventually decided to merge with Publicis.
Mr Maurice Levy, chairman of Publicis, said that the merger 'will reinforce
our position in almost every country and will enable us for the first time
to have a strong agency in New York'.
