FT  19 OCT 93 / UK Company News: Ewart falls into the red and passes
dividend
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
AN EXCEPTIONAL provision together with higher interest costs left Ewart, the
Northern Ireland-based property developer, with pre-tax losses of Pounds
155,721 for the year to end-April.
The exceptional item amounted to Pounds 279,377 and represented the cost of
an extraordinary meeting. Interest charges took some Pounds 200,000 more at
Pounds 949,493.
Earnings per share fell to 0.44p (1.18p) and, like the interim, the final is
also passed - last year a total of 0.75p was paid.
Directors said the investment market was strengthening with demand
outstripping supply of well covenanted properties in prime loc-ations.
They considered the timing of the company's entry into the investment market
in the UK to have been right and said properties acquired were performing
well.
