the acquisition of Frozen Herbs.
Consideration comprises an initial Pounds 1.75m cash and a further
profit-related amount, also in cash, to a maximum total of Pounds 3m.
Suffolk-based Frozen Herbs supplies leading UK food manufacturers with a
range of fresh frozen herbs.
In the 12 months to September 30 1992 it made pre-tax profits, before
exceptional management charges, of Pounds 459,000 on turnover of Pounds
1.84m.
Net assets at that date amounted to Pounds 193,000.
</TEXT>
