FT  19 OCT 93 / Expansion of gas production in the southern North Sea
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT CORZINE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
LIBERALISATION of the British gas market has persuaded Amoco, the US oil
company with extensive North Sea operations, to embark on a Pounds 160m
investment programme to expand gas production in the southern North Sea,
Robert Corzine writes.
The company said the investment would extend the life of the Indefatigable
field 60 miles off Norfolk. It would also open up four smaller gas fields in
the same area.
Mr Mike Ambrose, Amoco commercial manager, said the expansion was only made
possible because British Gas was willing to renegotiate the original
depletion contract, which gave it sole access to all the gas in the area.
The new arrangement guarantees British Gas additional supplies, while
allowing Amoco to sell surplus gas in the open market.
