FT  19 OCT 93 / Engineering companies suffer in the north
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By IAN HAMILTON FAZEY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
ENGINEERING companies in South Yorkshire and the north Midlands are
experiencing weakening prices and reduced margins, says the Sheffield
association of the Engineering Employers' Federation, Ian Hamilton Fazey
writes.
The association, which covers one of the UK's most intense concentrations of
manufacturing industry, says a survey of 107 companies has shown nearly 30
per cent suffering falling profitabil-ity in the past three months.
Mr Nicholas Kemp, the association's director, said yesterday: 'There is
intense competition both at home and abroad for engineering business, and
some prices have weakened. Almost a quarter of companies say prices are
worse and some are indicating worsening cashflow.'
