circuits only, rounded to the nearest million MiTT.
* Indicates data for North American carriers include continental
traffic. Stentor was formerly Telecom Canada; Stentor traffic is for US
and Mexico only of which around 70 per cent was originated by Bell
Canada. For Italy, Iritel (formerly ASST) handles intra-continental
traffic only. Italcable carries overseas traffic. For DBP Telekom, 1992
data includes outgoing traffic from the former East Germany. For
Netherlands PTT, 1992 data is for financial rather than physical
traffic. Telia AB was formerly Televerket.
 ----------------------------------------------------------------------
Note: BT, KDD, Hong Kong Telecom and Mercury data are for the fiscal
year (April 1992 to March 1993).
 ----------------------------------------------------------------------
Source: TeleGeography Inc., Washington, 1993.
 ----------------------------------------------------------------------
</TEXT>
